Jim Taylor


Dealer Principal






jim@troyford.com


Troy Ford's Dealer Principal/Owner, Jim Taylor, was born in Eastern Kentucky and grew up in Norwood, OH--where his father worked for General Motors. He graduated from Eastern Kentucky University in 1964, then began working for Ford Motor Company--who relocated him (as part of a promotion) to Detroit, MI in 1973. He went on to purchase the Troy Ford dealership in 1977.He has three children with his wife, Carolyn, whom he married in August of 1964. The couple also currently have 5 grandchildren.When he finds free time he enjoys horse racing, as well as all of the activities his grandchildren are involved in. He serves on several community boards and is involved with missions performed by the Ginghamsburg Methodist Church.
